


Day-12 - Deploy and Expose your First App on AWS
====================================================



GitHub Repository Used for the App Deployment
Link - https://github.com/verma-kunal/AWS-Session



Go to AWS Console Create a EC2 Instance  With Instance Type as t2.micro


sudo apt update


sudo apt install git


git --version

Output = git version 2.34.1


sudo apt install nodejs -y



node -v

Output = v12.22.9



sudo apt install npm


npm --version

Output = 8.5.1




git clone https://github.com/verma-kunal/AWS-Session




Create a .env file and Enter the Below Mentioned Variables

vim .env


DOMAIN="http://localhost:3000"
PORT=3000
STATIC_DIR="./client"

PUBLISHABLE_KEY="YOUR_PUBLISHABLE_KEY"
SECRET_KEY="YOUR_SECRET_KEY"





Note - To get the PUBLISHABLE_KEY & SECRET_KEY use below Link 
Link - https://dashboard.stripe.com/login




npm install


npm run start



Go to the Browser Add the Public IP of the Instance and :3000  To Access the Application




